## Example Interaction
------------------------
Player X enter: 0 0

X |   | 
  |   | 
  |   | 

Player O enter: 1 1

X |   | 
  | O | 
  |   | 

Player X enter: 0 1

X | X | 
  | O | 
  |   | 

Player O enter: 2 2

X | X | 
  | O | 
  |   | O

Player X enter: 0 2

X | X | X
  | O | 
  |   | 

Player X has won!

## Game Rules
------------------
- Player X always starts the game.
- Players take turns entering row and column numbers (0, 1, or 2) to place their mark.
- The game ends when either player wins or all cells are filled (in which case it results in a tie).
- The winner is determined by having three marks (X or O) in a row, column, or diagonal.

